##################
# model metadata #
##################

#---
# Title: A library of rules for interactions in the AMPK-MTORC1-ULK1 regulatory network
# Description: 
#   
# Contributors:
#  - Joern Dengjel
#  - Kristin E. Dittenhafer-Reed
#  - William S. Hlavacek
#  - Jeffrey P. MacKeigan
#  - Katie R. Martin
#  - Joshua L. Schipper
# Inputs:
#  - amino acids
#  - growth factor
#  - glucose
#  - AZD8055 (ATP-competitive inhibitor of MTOR)
#  - rapamycin
#  - The parameter "AA_conc_uM" can be adjusted to vary the abundance of Rag dimers
#    containing GTP-loaded RagA and GDP-loaded RagC, which affects MTORC1 activity.
#  - The parameter "growth_factor_conc_pM" can be adjusted to vary the abundance of
#    lysosomal GTP-loaded RHEB, which affects MTORC1 activity.
#  - The parameter "glucose_conc_mM" can be adjusted to vary the [AMP]:[ATP] ratio,
#    which affects AMPK activity.
#  - Set the Boolean parameter "AZD8055_isPresent" to 1 to indicate that AZD8055 is present.
#    The parameter "AZD8055_conc_nM" determines the concentration of AZD8055.
#  - Set the Boolean parameter "rapamycin_isPresent" to 1 to indicate that rapamycin is present.
#    The parameter "rapamycin_conc_nM" determines the concentration of rapamycin.
# Proteins:
#   ========================= =========================
#  | Common name             | HGNC nomenclature       |
#   =======================  =========================
#  | FKBP12                  | FKBP1A                  |
#  | mTOR                    | MTOR                    |
#  | Raptor                  | RPTOR                   |
#  | mLST8 (aka GbetaL)      | MLST8                   |
#  | S6K1                    | RPS6KB1                 |
#  | 4E-BP1                  | EIF4EBP1                |
#  | Ragulator               | ---                     |
#  |  LAMTOR1 (nee p18)      | LAMTOR1                 |
#  |  LAMTOR2 (nee p14)      | LAMTOR2                 |
#  |  LAMTOR3 (nee MP1)      | LAMTOR3                 |
#  |  LAMTOR4 (nee C7orf59)  | LAMTOR4                 |
#  |  LAMTOR5 (nee HBXIP)    | LAMTOR5                 |
#  | RagA                    | RRAGA                   |
#  | RagC                    | RRAGC                   |
#  | Rheb                    | RHEB                    |
#  | TSC2                    | TSC2                    |
#  | AMPK                    | ---                     |
#  |  AMPK-alpha1            | PRKAA1                  |
#  |  AMPK-beta1             | PRKAB1                  |
#  |  AMPK-beta2             | PRKAB2                  |
#  |  AMPK-gamma1            | PRKAG1                  |
#  | LKB1                    | STK11                   |
#  | Atg13 (mATG13)          | ATG13                   |
#  | Atg101                  | ATG101                  |
#  | FIP200                  | RB1CC1                  |
#  | ULK1 (mATG1)            | ULK1                    |
#  | AMBRA1                  | AMBRA1                  |
#  | Beclin-1 (mATG6)        | BECN1                   |
#   ========================= =========================
# Phosphosites:
#  - S792 in RPTOR, substrate of AMPK
#  - S855/S859 (lumped together) in RPTOR, substrates of ULK1
#  - T389 in S6K1, substrate of MTORC1
#  - T37/T47 (lumped together) in 4E-BP1, rapamycin-resistant substrates of MTORC1
#  - S65/T70 (lumped together) in 4E-BP1, rapamycin-sensitive substrates of MTORC1
#  - S1387 in TSC2, substrate of AMPK
#  - T183 (aka T172) in the alpha subunit of AMPK, substrate of LKB1
#  - the "Dock" component of AMPK, substrate(s) of ULK1
#  - the "Site3" component of the gamma subunit of AMPK, substrate(s) of ULK1
#  - S259 in ATG13, substrate of MTORC1
#  - T180 in ULK1, substrate of ULK1
#  - S317 in ULK1, substrate of AMPK
#  - S556 in ULK1, substrate of AMPK
#  - S758 in ULK1, substrate of MTORC1
#  - S465/S635 (lumped together), substrates of ULK1
#  - S15 in Beclin-1, substrate of ULK1
# Cell lines:
#  - A549 cells
#  - HEK293 cells
#  - U2OS cells
#  - HeLa S3 cells
#  - HeLa Kyoto cells
#  comments:
#   - A database of measured protein copy numbers is included so that the
#     model may be tuned for A549, HEK293, U2OS, HeLa S3, or HeLa Kyoto cells.
#     The default protein copy number settings are for U2OS cells.
#   - The model has 26 cell line-specific protein copy number parameters:
#       FKBP1A_cpc, MTOR_cpc, RPTOR_cpc, MLST8_cpc, RPS6KB1_cpc, EIF4EBP1_cpc, 
#       LAMTOR1_cpc, LAMTOR2_cpc, LAMTOR3_cpc, LAMTOR4_cpc, LAMTOR5_cpc, 
#       RRAGA_cpc, RRAGC_cpc, RHEB_cpc, TSC2_cpc,
#       PRKAA1_cpc, PRKAB1_cpc, PRKAB2_cpc, PRKAG1_cpc, STK11_cpc,
#       ATG13_cpc, ATG101_cpc, RB1CC1_cpc, ULK1_cpc, AMBRA1_cpc, and BECN1_cpc.
#   - Other model parameters, such as Vcyt (cytosolic volume), Dlys (lysosome size),
#     and Nlys (number of lysosomes), may be tuned for specific cell lines. Yet other
#     model parameters, such as Vecf (the volume of extracellular fluid surrounding a
#     cell in culture, on average), may be tuned for specific experimental conditions.
# Compartments:
#  - ecf: extracellular fluid
#  - cyt: cytosol
#  - lys: lysosomal membrane (facing the cytosol)
#  comments:
#   - The model is formulated for a single cell. Three compartments are considered:
#     the extracellular fluid surrounding a cell, the cytosol, and lysosomal membrane
#     surfaces facing the cytosol.
# References:
#  - Alayev A, ..., Holz MK (2015) Oncogene doi: 10.1038/onc.2015.414 [PMID: 26522726]
#  - Avruch J, ..., Kikkawa U (2009) Biochem Soc Trans 37: 223-226. [PMID: 19143636]
